"```json\n{\n  \"Coding Problem\": \"Complete the function that accepts a valid string and returns an integer.\\n\\nWait, that would be too easy! Every character of the string should be converted to the hex value of its ascii code, then the result should be the sum of the numbers in the hex strings (ignore letters).\\n\\n## Examples\\n```\\n\\\"Yo\\\" ==> \\\"59 6f\\\" ==> 5 + 9 + 6 = 20\\n\\\"Hello, World!\\\"  ==> 91\\n\\\"Forty4Three\\\"    ==> 113\\n```\",\n  \"Ground Truth Solution\": \"def hex_hash(code):\\n\\treturn sum((int(d) for c in code for d in hex(ord(c)) if d.isdigit()))\",\n  \"LLM CoT Steps Breakdown\": \"- Understanding the Problem: The problem requires converting each character of the input string to its hexadecimal ASCII representation. Then, sum all the digit characters present in these hex strings to produce the final result.\\n- Decomposing the Task: The problem can be broken down into character-by-character conversion, extraction of hex values, digit filtering and summation. \\n- Algorithm Selection: The algorithm requires iterating through each character, converting it to its ASCII value and then to its hex representation. From the hex string extract the digits and then sum up the digits to return the final integer value.\\n- Edge Case Identification: Empty string or strings with no digits should return zero.\",\n  \"LLM Questions\": [\n    \"What is the process of converting each character to its hexadecimal representation?\",\n    \"How would you iterate through the string and convert each character?\",\n    \"How can you extract the hex value from the ascii value of each character?\",\n    \"How would you handle non-digit characters that are part of hex strings?\",\n    \"How should edge cases like an empty input string be treated?\"\n  ],\n  \"Expected Answers to LLM Questions\": [\n    \"The process involves getting the ASCII (numerical) value of the character using `ord()`, and then converting it to its hexadecimal representation using `hex()`.\",\n    \"You can iterate through each character using a simple `for` loop: `for c in code:`.\",\n    \"By applying the `hex()` function directly on the ASCII value obtained from `ord(c)` function.\",\n    \"You can filter out the letters from the hex string by only considering the digit characters using `isdigit()` method.\",\n    \"An empty input string should return a zero, as there are no characters to convert and sum.\"\n  ]\n}\n```"